Lucapa Diamond Company has received the 2021 interim dividend payment that has been approved by the shareholders of Sociedade Mineira Do Lulo. The US$3.6 million payment was in respect of Lucapaâ€™s 40% associate share of the approved US$10.0 million. The 2021 dividend was declared by shareholders following a record year for Lulo where record volumes processed, and carats recovered resulted in revenues of US$78.1 million being achieved at US$2,808 per carat. New Azilian is due a bullet principal payment of A$10.5 million on 28 February 2022. This loan was attracting a 9.8% interest charge. The Company will make the principal payment as scheduled. SML shareholders also approved a US$10.0 million capital loan repayment. The protocols for repatriating the capital loan repayment are already in process. The Company will update the market upon receipt of the loan repayment.